>I am confused. AFAICT, the majority of movie piracy today takes place
>via DivX from DVD's. How does Macrovision even play a role in this?

Macrovision only prevents some VCRs from recording DVD content, a 
decreasing market.  Video "correctors" are widely available for under $60 
to neuter Macrovision protection.

All DVD ripping SW bypasses any Macrovision protection.

